\n< Serena >Lord Mary... Ah, oh my, um... I apologize
for interrupting...

\n< Mary >Oh my, calling it an interruption...
Serena-chan, welcome.

\n< Mary >This child hasn't finished eating yet, so I
can't let go of my hands... But if you
don't mind, would you like to talk on
the phone?

\n< Serena >Ah... um... Well then, if you don't mind,
I'll take you up on your offer.

\n< Serena >Oh, you seem lively. Is your daughter doing
well too?

\n< Mary >Yes, thanks to that, both my child and I are
doing well.

\n< Mary >Well, it's certainly tough. She cries and
wets herself all the time, day and
night, without a care.
\n< Serena >But it looks fun.

\n< Mary >Yes, it's really tough... but more than
that, she's even more adorable, you
know...

\n< Mary >Watching her suckling on my breast and earnestly
drinking milk like this...

\n< Mary >I feel like I was born to meet this
child. That's what I believe. So, no
matter what happens, I'll be fine.
\n< Mary >For now, you see.

\n< Serena >Um... Mary-sama, if I may ask... does it not
hurt when you breastfeed?
\n< Mary >Hurt? It doesn't hurt... Ah, um... haha.
\n< Serena >Huh?

\n< Mary >That's right, Serena-chan is also at that age.
She must be confused by all the changes
happening to her body, right?
\n< Serena >...Hmm. I'm... confused.

\n< Serena >Lately, my chest has been hurting... I wonder
if I'm sick...

\n< Mary >Hehehe, don't worry. That's normal. It means
Serena-chan is also getting ready to
breastfeed a baby like this.

\n< Serena >Breast milk... will it come out? Could it be
that pain...!?

\n< Mary >Ahh, umm. It's not like it comes out right
away. Breast milk naturally starts to
come out after the baby is born, you
know.
\n< Serena >I-I see...

\n< Mary >The preparations for that have already
begun inside Serena-chan's body. It
means you're growing up. It means you're
ready to become a mother.
\n< Serena >To become an adult...

\n< Mary >So, there's no need to panic. It's natural
to be surprised at first. It happens to
everyone.
\n< Serena >....

\n< Mary >Breasts are for the baby. Right now, Serena-
chan's breasts are working hard for the
sake of future babies.
\n< Mary >So please take good care of them.
\n< Serena >Specifically, what should I do...?

\n< Mary >Don't touch them too much. Just because it
feels good, doesn't mean you should play
with them.
\n< Serena >It doesn't feel good, but...

\n< Mary >Next is choosing underwear. It's best to
choose something that tightly wraps
around your breasts. It may be expensive
though...

\n< Serena >Yes, I did buy some, but they just don't
feel right...

\n< Mary >It may feel strange at first, but you'll
get used to it quickly.

\n< Mary >And also, make sure to wear something that
fits your body properly. As your body
grows, your breasts will also become
bigger, so it's better to consult with a
trusted adult about it.
\n< Serena >To an adult person... Hmm.

\n< Mary >But when it still hurts no matter what, you
should pray to God.
\n< Serena >To God?

\n< Mary >Yes. Thank you for making my body grow every
day.

\n< Mary >Because that pain is like a sign from God,
saying that it's okay to give birth to a
baby and be happy.

\n< Mary >Well, if you do that, well, it will be
painful... but you'll stop worrying
about it. You'll understand that it's
not a bad pain.
\n< Serena >I see...

\n< Serena >It was helpful. It was really helpful.
Thank you, Mary.
\n< Mary >No, you're welcome.
\n< Serena >Well.
\n< Mary >Oh, are you leaving already?

\n< Serena >Yes. There are still things I need to do. My
worries have disappeared, so now it's
time for work.
\n< Mary >Yes, then please come again.
\n< Serena >Ah, well then, see you again.
\n< Mary >Please come again, Serena-chan.

\n< Mary >Serena-san... I heard. I can only pray for you, but
please come back safely...
\n< Serena >Excuse me--.

\n< Female >Oh my! Welcome! Welcome, little
adventurer!
\n< Serena >Ah, ah...
\n< Serena >It's good to see you're doing well.

\n< Female >What's wrong?

\n< Female >Oh, speaking of which, I haven't introduced
myself yet. I was also in a hurry at
that time... My name is Mary.

\n< Serena >Ah, Lord Mary. Nice to meet you. I am
Serena.
\n< Female >Nice to meet you, Serena-chan.

\n< Mary >Jean... My husband will be coming home soon. If
you don't mind, would you like to have
dinner together?

\n< Serena >I think I'll refrain from that. Just
having some tea would be enough...

\n< Serena >No, tea is strange. Besides, Lord Mary,
that...
\n< Mary >What is it?

\n< Serena >Um, shouldn't you be resting? Your belly
looks very big and you seem to be
struggling.

\n< Serena >Actually, I just came here to say a quick
hello...

\n< Mary >Oh, you're saying the same thing as Jean,
huh?

\n< Mary >But it's okay, I've been with this belly
for a long time. I've gotten used to it.

\n< Serena >Have you gotten used to it, going out and
almost being attacked by goblins?

\n< Mary >Ahh, don't say it. I really... really want
some mountain vegetables...

\n< Mary >My husband got really angry at me. He was
furious.

\n< Mary >This is the most serious I've ever been
scolded. I felt his love...
\n< Serena >I-I see...

\n< Mary >But being able to laugh about it like this
is all thanks to you, Serena-chan.

\n< Mary >You are the benefactor of me, my husband,
and our baby.
\n< Mary >Thank you again, Serena-chan. Really.
\n< Mary >Ahh, I'm glad I could say it.
\n< Serena >....

\n< Serena >Huh? Your husband... and a baby? Do you have
children? I don't see any...
\n< Mary >Hm?... Ahh...

\n< Mary >Um, well? The baby... is here. Inside my
belly.
\n< Serena >...What?

\n< Mary >...Wow, that's amazing. It's like a hidden
treasure. Can I just go ahead and tell
her about it?
\n< Mary >But I'll tell you.

\n< Mary >You know, Serena-chan. Women, you see? They
grow babies inside their bellies like
this.

\n< Serena >Huh?... That's the first time I've heard of
it...

\n< Serena >The baby... inside your belly? H-How...?
How did it get in there?
\n< Mary >Wha...what...uh, umm.

\n< Mary >The baby, you know? When a man and a woman
really, really love each other, they
think about each other a lot and...

\n< Mary >One day, it comes into a woman's belly.
It's a gift from God.
\n< Serena >Just by thinking?
\n< Mary >Um...well, you see...it's not just that...

\n< Mary >No, this story might be a little too early
for Serena-chan...

\n< Mary >The stamen and pistil...they come
together...um...huh? I wonder if my
parents will get mad at me for this?
\n< Serena >Huh?

\n< Mary >Anyway, anyway, you know? The crystallization
of love between a man and a woman is a
baby.

\n< Mary >At first, it's much smaller... Women take
a lot of time to slowly and gradually
raise the baby, making it grow bigger.

\n< Mary >Well, you see, it's very difficult... but
it's something that has a lot of value.
It's the most valuable thing in this
world.
\n< Serena >It has value...?

\n< Mary >Well, you see...that's right, isn't it? I was
also born because my mom and dad loved
each other.

\n< Mary >My mom and dad were also born because
their moms and dads loved each other.

\n< Mary >Even my father's father's father and my
mother's mother's mother's mother...

\n< Mary >From a time so long ago that it feels like
my mind is drifting away... I love you,
I cherish you. That's how I feel.

\n< Mary >It has been transmitted without
interruption even once.

\n< Mary >And then my husband was born, and I was
born...

\n< Mary >And then, we love each other, saying I love
you. We give birth to a child and pass
on that love to them.
\n< Mary >I love you, I cherish you.

\n< Mary >...This child will surely pass it on to their
children someday. And their children
will continue to pass it on, forever and
ever.
\n< Mary >That's why the whole world is made of love.
\n< Mary >I'm so, so happy... I'm glad you're here.

\n< Mary >People give birth to and raise children in
order to convey those feelings to each
other.
\n< Serena >Me too...?
\n< Mary >Of course!

\n< Mary >Serena-chan, me, and everyone else, we are all in a
big, big love story.

\n< Mary >Saying I love you and I cherish you a lot is
what made you, Serena-chan, into Serena-
chan.

\n< Mary >Because if it wasn't like that, you wouldn't
have become such an adorable Serena-
chan.

\n< Mary >That's why Serena-chan, too, has a big love
and I love you, I cherish you.

\n< Mary >And someday, I will have someone I want to
convey it to, and children I want to
convey it to.
\n< Serena >I see...
\n< Serena >...I've never thought about it that way before.

\n< Serena >I used to think that children are born
out of obligation.

\n< Serena >In order to continue the family and leave
behind blood, my father and mother
created me for that purpose. Therefore,
as their child, I have a duty to fulfill
their expectations.

\n< Serena >Well, in my family, there is already my older
sister. She is much more talented than
me, many times over. It's not a problem
even if I'm not there.

\n< Serena >That's why I thought about how I can fulfill
my duty. As a support, even more than
just being a spare for my older
sister...
\n< Mary >Serena-chan.
\n< Serena >Huh?

\n< Mary >That is absolutely, absolutely, absolutely
wrong.

\n< Mary >No parent thinks that having a child and
raising them is an obligation.

\n< Mary >When I was still my father and mother's
daughter, I didn't understand it well
either.

\n< Mary >But now that I've become a mother to this
child, I understand. I can say this
much.

\n< Mary >Children are pure joy for parents. They are love
itself. For the sake of their smiles,
for the sake of their happiness, parents
are willing to sacrifice their bodies,
their lives, and even their souls
without hesitation.

\n< Mary >So, you know? Please don't say such
things...

\n< Mary >Sometimes parents may not be able to express it
well, but always, no matter when, they
think about their children... mmm...!
\n< Serena >Lord Mary?

\n< Mary >Ouch... th-tha...that. What is this... I
wonder...

\n< Mary >Maybe I got a little tired from talking so
much...?
